href=\"ISic003457.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; Photo R.J.A. Wilson\" src=\"ISic003457-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>  \u003Cspan>Text of Silvestrini 2014\u003C/span>  \u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>[Lucius Plinius Rufus, son of Lucius] propraetorian legate, praetor designate, [gave this as a gift] to Venus Equestris\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>Silvestrini 2014 plausibly suggests that this is a dedication set up by L. Plinius L.f. Rufus, legatus pro praetore of Sextus Pompeius and praetor designate for 33 BC, already attested at Lilybaeum in ILLRP 426 = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic000007\" target=\"_blank\">ISic000007\u003C/a>. The inscription is referenced within AE 2007.678-679, although neither lemma there concerns this text.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> 2014.537 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001283\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001283\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Silvestrini 2014 211-215 no.2 fig.5-6 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001581\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001581\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Silvestrini 2024 424-425, figs. 438-439 \u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"handnote\"> Line 1  55  \u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribu